id: pm-6vv6
title: "writeFileAtomic cross-device rename safety: handle EXDEV when tmp and target are on different mounts"
description: "writeFileAtomic writes a .tmp file in the same directory as the target then renames. If the item store is on a different filesystem mount than the temp-file directory (e.g. symlinked paths, container bind mounts, or network FS), fs.rename raises EXDEV (cross-device link not permitted). There is no fallback to copy+unlink."
type: Issue
status: in_progress
priority: 2
tags[3]: "area:storage",correctness,durability
created_at: "2026-06-07T10:02:44.972Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-07T13:01:27.891Z"
assignee: codex-active-pm-cycle-20260607
author: audit-data-agent
acceptance_criteria: "- `writeFileAtomic` catches `EXDEV` and falls back to: write to a tmp in `os.tmpdir()`, copy to target, unlink tmp\n- OR falls back to a non-atomic `writeFile` with a warning so the file is never left corrupt\n- Both `fs-utils.ts` and the LanceDB snapshot writer handle this case\n- Unit test covering the EXDEV code path (mock `rename` to throw EXDEV)"
parent: pm-o2kc
risk: low
confidence: high
